# ── Spotify API credentials ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a free app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#
# Steps:
#   1. Click "Create app"
#   2. Fill in any name/description
#   3. Under "Redirect URIs" add:  http://127.0.0.1:6767/api/spotify/callback
#      (⚠️  localhost is NOT allowed — use the literal IP 127.0.0.1)
#   4. Under "Which API/SDKs are you planning to use?" tick Web API only
#   5. Copy your Client ID and Client Secret below
#
# After starting the container, go to Settings → Connect Spotify Account
# to complete the OAuth login. Tokens are stored in the container volume
# and auto-refreshed.
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT — Spotify API restriction (November 2024):
#   Spotify blocked the playlist tracks endpoint for apps in Development Mode,
#   even with a valid OAuth token. You need to configure the sp_dc cookie in
#   the Settings UI after setup — see README § "Set the sp_dc cookie" for
#   step-by-step instructions. Without it, Sync will return a 403 error.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# ── Music output directory ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute path on your HOST machine that will be mounted into the container.
MUSIC_DIR=/absolute/path/to/your/music/folder

# ── YouTube cookies (optional but recommended) ────────────────────────────
# If you see "Sign in to confirm you're not a bot" errors, export your
# YouTube cookies and mount them into the container.
#
# How to export:
#   1. Install the "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" extension in Chrome/Firefox
#   2. Go to https://www.youtube.com while logged in
#   3. Click the extension icon and export cookies.txt
#   4. Set COOKIES_PATH to the absolute path of that file:
#
# COOKIES_PATH=/absolute/path/to/cookies.txt
#
# Leave commented out (or empty) to skip — a harmless empty placeholder
# file will be mounted instead.
